{% extends 'layouts/page.njk' %}

{% block content %}
  <div class="govuk-grid-row">
    <div class="govuk-grid-column-two-thirds">

      <h1 class="govuk-heading-xl">Accessibility statement for AI Content Review</h1>

      <p class="govuk-body">This accessibility statement applies to the AI Content Review service, an internal Defra staff tool available to users with a Defra Microsoft (Azure Active Directory) account.</p>

      <p class="govuk-body">This service is run by the Department for Environment, Food &amp; Rural Affairs (Defra). We want as many people as possible to be able to use this service.</p>

      <h2 class="govuk-heading-l">Using this service</h2>

      <p class="govuk-body">This service is run by Defra. We want as many people as possible to be able to use this service. For example, that means you should be able to:</p>

      <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
        <li>change colours, contrast levels and fonts using browser or operating system settings</li>
        <li>zoom in up to 300% without the text spilling off the screen</li>
        <li>navigate the entire service using just a keyboard</li>
        <li>navigate the service using speech recognition software</li>
        <li>listen to the service using a screen reader (including the most recent versions of JAWS, NVDA and VoiceOver)</li>
      </ul>

      <p class="govuk-body">We've also made the text in the service as simple as possible to understand.</p>

      <p class="govuk-body">If you have a disability, <a href="https://mcmw.abilitynet.org.uk/" class="govuk-link" rel="noreferrer noopener" target="_blank">AbilityNet has advice on making your device easier to use (opens in new tab)</a>.</p>

      <h2 class="govuk-heading-l">How accessible this service is</h2>

      <p class="govuk-body">We believe this service is fully accessible. The AI review results page uses pale blue coloured highlights with additional text indicators — each highlighted issue is a link with an accessible label (for example, "Issue 1: plain-english") and each improvement item displays a visible category badge. Colour is not used as the sole means of conveying information.</p>

      <p class="govuk-body">The AI-generated review output is loaded asynchronously. Screen reader users will be notified when the review is ready, but the experience may vary across different assistive technologies.</p>

      <h2 class="govuk-heading-l">Feedback and contact information</h2>

      <p class="govuk-body">If you have difficulty using this service or need information in a different format, you can <a href="https://forms.office.com/e/yA5mQ2kEb3?origin=lprLink" class="govuk-link" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">contact us using our feedback form (opens in new tab)</a>.</p>

      <p class="govuk-body">We'll consider your request and get back to you within 5 working days.</p>

      <h2 class="govuk-heading-l">Reporting accessibility problems with this service</h2>

      <p class="govuk-body">We're always looking to improve the accessibility of this service. If you find any problems not listed on this page, or think we're not meeting accessibility requirements, <a href="https://forms.office.com/e/yA5mQ2kEb3?origin=lprLink" class="govuk-link" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">report the accessibility problem using our feedback form (opens in new tab)</a>.</p>

      <h2 class="govuk-heading-l">Enforcement procedure</h2>

      <p class="govuk-body">The Equality and Human Rights Commission (EHRC) is responsible for enforcing the Public Sector Bodies (Websites and Mobile Applications) (No. 2) Accessibility Regulations 2018 (the 'accessibility regulations'). If you're not happy with how we respond to your complaint, <a href="https://www.equalityadvisoryservice.com/" class="govuk-link" rel="noreferrer noopener" target="_blank">contact the Equality Advisory and Support Service (EASS) (opens in new tab)</a>.</p>

      <h2 class="govuk-heading-l">Technical information about this service's accessibility</h2>

      <p class="govuk-body">Defra is committed to making this service accessible, in accordance with the Public Sector Bodies (Websites and Mobile Applications) (No. 2) Accessibility Regulations 2018.</p>

      <h3 class="govuk-heading-m">Compliance status</h3>

      <p class="govuk-body">This service is fully compliant with the <a href="https://www.w3.org/TR/WCAG21/" class="govuk-link" rel="noreferrer noopener" target="_blank">Web Content Accessibility Guidelines version 2.1 AA standard (opens in new tab)</a>.</p>

      <h2 class="govuk-heading-l">Non-accessible content</h2>

      <p class="govuk-body">We are not aware of any non-accessible content in this service at this time. If you find a problem, please <a href="https://forms.office.com/e/yA5mQ2kEb3?origin=lprLink" class="govuk-link" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">report it using our feedback form (opens in new tab)</a>.</p>

      <h2 class="govuk-heading-l">Disproportionate burden</h2>

      <p class="govuk-body">We have not made any claims of disproportionate burden for this service.</p>

      <h2 class="govuk-heading-l">How we tested this service</h2>

      <p class="govuk-body">This service was last tested on 10 February 2026. The test was carried out internally by the Defra Service Optimisation team using the Axe and WAVE automated accessibility testing tools, covering all key user journeys including sign-in, content submission (text, URL and document upload), review results and review history.</p>

      <p class="govuk-body">The service is built using the <a href="https://design-system.service.gov.uk/" class="govuk-link" rel="noreferrer noopener" target="_blank">GOV.UK Design System (opens in new tab)</a> and GOV.UK Frontend, which are tested for accessibility by the GOV.UK Design System team.</p>

      <h2 class="govuk-heading-l">What we're doing to improve accessibility</h2>

      <p class="govuk-body">We are working to:</p>

      <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
        <li>carry out a full manual accessibility audit, including testing with assistive technology users</li>
        <li>address any issues raised through user feedback promptly</li>
      </ul>

      <p class="govuk-body">This statement was prepared on 12 February 2026. It was last reviewed on 27 April 2026.</p>

    </div>
  </div>
{% endblock %}
